# pymacaron-async An extension of pymacaron seamlessly adding asynchronous task execution based on celery/Redis. See more at [pymacaron.com](http://pymacaron.com/async.html) NOTE: tests for pymacaron-async are located in pymacaron-helloworld. This is temporary and needs to be fixed. ## Author Erwan Lemonnier
